♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

6
00:01:29.550 --> 00:01:34.486
♪ Happy birthday,
dear Ronnie ♪


7
00:01:34.488 --> 00:01:39.024
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

8
00:01:39.026 --> 00:01:40.259
Happy birthday.

9
00:01:44.098 --> 00:01:46.098
Ah, thank you, thank you.

10
00:01:46.100 --> 00:01:48.167
- To the band.
- To the band.


11
00:01:48.169 --> 00:01:49.735
- To Ronnie's birthday.
- Ronnie.


12
00:01:49.737 --> 00:01:52.104
- To Ronnie.
- To Ronnie.


13
00:01:52.106 --> 00:01:55.407
Do you always celebrate
the night before?


14
00:01:55.409 --> 00:01:57.743
I was born at 3 a.m.
If I wait till tomorrow,


15
00:01:57.745 --> 00:02:00.045
by the time I wake up,
it'll have been over.


16
00:02:00.047 --> 00:02:03.015
So keep drinking
till 3:00 then?


17
00:02:03.017 --> 00:02:06.085
Can't. Things to do.

18
00:02:19.233 --> 00:02:21.266
I love you.

19
00:02:21.268 --> 00:02:23.335
I love you.

20
00:02:50.064 --> 00:02:52.531
What are you taking?

21
00:02:52.533 --> 00:02:54.400
Just a sleeping pill.

22
00:02:55.703 --> 00:02:57.236
Had a few rough nights lately.

23
00:02:57.238 --> 00:02:59.338
Why didn't you tell me?

24
00:02:59.340 --> 00:03:00.472
It doesn't matter.

25
00:03:03.644 --> 00:03:04.743
Hey.

26
00:03:10.217 --> 00:03:13.252
What's going on?

27
00:03:13.254 --> 00:03:17.790
We won't see each other
when I go on tour.


28
00:03:17.792 --> 00:03:20.559
Babe, you're a rock chick.

29
00:03:20.561 --> 00:03:23.195
This is what you do.

30
00:03:23.197 --> 00:03:25.697
I can't follow you
around the world, can I?


31
00:03:25.699 --> 00:03:30.235
And you're happy
just to keep going like this?


32
00:03:32.139 --> 00:03:33.572
What?

33
00:03:33.574 --> 00:03:35.207
Forget it.

34
00:03:37.078 --> 00:03:38.577
I'm screwing up your birthday.

35
00:03:38.579 --> 00:03:42.648
No. I wanna know
what you're talking about.


36
00:03:42.650 --> 00:03:45.250
You never stop.

37
00:03:45.252 --> 00:03:48.087
When you're working on your art,
it takes you over.


38
00:03:52.359 --> 00:03:54.860
Like some kind of beast.

39
00:03:56.263 --> 00:03:58.130
What, so this is
about me now?


40
00:03:58.132 --> 00:03:59.798
No.

41
00:03:59.800 --> 00:04:02.701
I'm the same.
Exactly the same.


42
00:04:02.703 --> 00:04:05.270
But sometimes,
it just gets to me,


43
00:04:05.272 --> 00:04:08.340
that we never have time
to be together.


44
00:04:22.556 --> 00:04:24.656
Ronnie, your scar is bleeding.

45
00:04:27.628 --> 00:04:29.895
Wow. You really
did a number on me.


46
00:04:29.897 --> 00:04:32.731
- Has it ever done that before?
- No.


47
00:04:32.733 --> 00:04:35.601
I'd better get a plaster.
Be back.


48
00:06:45.466 --> 00:06:47.699
Happy birthday, darling.

49
00:06:50.271 --> 00:06:52.004
Thank you, Mum.

50
00:06:53.641 --> 00:06:55.307
How was Lena's gig?

51
00:06:55.309 --> 00:06:57.843
Great. I'm still feeling it.

52
00:06:57.845 --> 00:07:00.445
I saw her video on YouTube
in the store.


53
00:07:00.447 --> 00:07:02.547
Yeah? What did you think?

54
00:07:02.549 --> 00:07:04.283
Amazing.

55
00:07:04.285 --> 00:07:06.285
So when do I get
to see you guys?


56
00:07:06.287 --> 00:07:07.619
We can do tonight
if you like.


57
00:07:07.621 --> 00:07:08.654
Perfect.

58
00:07:08.656 --> 00:07:10.489
I made you a cake.

59
00:07:10.491 --> 00:07:12.491
Ooh, then we're
definitely coming.


60
00:07:14.595 --> 00:07:17.896
Something happened to me
last night.


61
00:07:17.898 --> 00:07:22.334
This whole huge painting
just came to me out of nowhere.


62
00:07:22.336 --> 00:07:27.306
It only hit me afterwards
that I started at 3 a.m.


63
00:07:27.308 --> 00:07:29.441
Exactly my birthday, right?

64
00:07:29.443 --> 00:07:31.410
Mm. Can I see it?

65
00:07:31.412 --> 00:07:32.878
Yeah, sure.

66
00:07:37.851 --> 00:07:40.952
Sorry. Do you have
an IT section?


67
00:07:40.954 --> 00:07:44.523
Yes, sure, follow me.
I'll be back, Mum.


68
00:08:26.667 --> 00:08:28.800
You sure she said tonight?

69
00:08:30.537 --> 00:08:31.970
Lights are on.

70
00:08:38.846 --> 00:08:40.045
Mum?

71
00:08:41.115 --> 00:08:43.014
Mum, it's me and Lena.

72
00:08:53.961 --> 00:08:57.129
Okay, thanks.
Yeah, I hope so too.


73
00:09:00.901 --> 00:09:02.567
Can't register
as missing yet.


74
00:09:02.569 --> 00:09:04.669
She has to be gone
for 48 hours.


75
00:09:04.671 --> 00:09:06.571
<i>Hi, this is Suleka.</i>

76
00:09:06.573 --> 00:09:08.940
<i>Leave a message,
and I'll get back to you.</i>


77
00:09:27.728 --> 00:09:29.861
Mum?

78
00:09:29.863 --> 00:09:31.563
<i>Is that Ronnie?</i>

79
00:09:31.565 --> 00:09:33.698
Yeah.

80
00:09:33.700 --> 00:09:35.700
<i>You're Suleka's son, right?</i>

81
00:09:35.702 --> 00:09:37.502
Yes. Who is this?

82
00:09:37.504 --> 00:09:41.139
<i>I'm AJ, your cousin.
Your Uncle Mohan's son.</i>


83
00:09:41.141 --> 00:09:43.041
<i>I'm calling from Kolkata.</i>

84
00:09:43.043 --> 00:09:44.910
<i>Ronnie, your mother's
in hospital.</i>


85
00:09:44.912 --> 00:09:46.812
<i>She was hit by a car.</i>

86
00:09:48.148 --> 00:09:50.715
What? In Kolkata?

87
00:09:50.717 --> 00:09:52.484
<i>Well, we don't
understand either.</i>


88
00:09:52.486 --> 00:09:53.852
<i>We didn't even know
she was in India</i>


89
00:09:53.854 --> 00:09:55.053
<i>until the hospital phoned.</i>

90
00:09:55.055 --> 00:09:56.788
Is she gonna be okay?

91
00:09:56.790 --> 00:09:59.958
<i>Well, Ronnie,
she's been kept in a coma.</i>


92
00:09:59.960 --> 00:10:03.028
<i>She has a blood clot
on her lung.</i>


93
00:10:03.030 --> 00:10:06.198
Uh, okay, okay, um...

94
00:10:06.200 --> 00:10:08.900
Look, I'm gonna search
for flights right now, okay?


95
00:10:08.902 --> 00:10:10.502
<i>Tell me when
you're getting in,</i>


96
00:10:10.504 --> 00:10:11.770
<i>and I'll be there
to get you.</i>


97
00:10:11.772 --> 00:10:13.171
Okay. Thank you.

98
00:10:21.215 --> 00:10:25.083
Mum said she never wanted
to go back to India.


99
00:10:25.085 --> 00:10:27.118
She said she never wanted
to see those people again.


100
00:10:36.797 --> 00:10:38.263
Ronnie!

101
00:10:38.265 --> 00:10:40.198
Are you AJ?

102
00:10:40.200 --> 00:10:43.668
I recognized you from the photo
on your Mum's phone.


103
00:10:43.670 --> 00:10:45.070
This way.

104
00:10:48.108 --> 00:10:49.774
First time here?

105
00:10:57.150 --> 00:10:58.917
Is my mother conscious yet?

106
00:10:58.919 --> 00:11:00.752
Mm-mm.

107
00:11:22.609 --> 00:11:25.110
No, no, no, no!
They'll all come for you.


108
00:11:27.915 --> 00:11:29.881
Unintelligent behavior.

109
00:11:50.637 --> 00:11:53.905
I managed to transfer your mum
to their special ward.


110
00:12:04.751 --> 00:12:06.985
Hi, Mum.

111
00:12:06.987 --> 00:12:09.154
It's me, Ronnie.

112
00:12:16.697 --> 00:12:17.896
Yes, sir.

113
00:12:21.635 --> 00:12:23.902
Shit. Are you the son
from England?


114
00:12:23.904 --> 00:12:25.670
That's right. Ronnie.

115
00:12:25.672 --> 00:12:27.305
Dr. Multlar.

116
00:12:27.307 --> 00:12:30.208
Look, Ronnie, I've got some
really good news for you.


117
00:12:30.210 --> 00:12:32.077
Early this morning,

118
00:12:32.079 --> 00:12:34.779
we managed to break down
your mother's blood clot.


119
00:12:34.781 --> 00:12:36.615
So that means...

120
00:12:36.617 --> 00:12:38.183
That means we'll have
to keep her in this state


121
00:12:38.185 --> 00:12:39.851
for another couple of days,

122
00:12:39.853 --> 00:12:43.788
and then we have hope
that she'll recover.


123
00:12:46.660 --> 00:12:49.194
Look, this is the time
when she needs to bathe her,


124
00:12:49.196 --> 00:12:52.998
and we also need
to run some tests, so...


125
00:12:54.234 --> 00:12:56.267
Doctor...

126
00:13:16.356 --> 00:13:19.057
So there's Latta, AJ's wife,

127
00:13:19.059 --> 00:13:21.359
and their kid Juma.

128
00:13:21.361 --> 00:13:22.394
Juma's really sweet, actually.

129
00:13:22.396 --> 00:13:24.663
<i>Really? How old is she?</i>

130
00:13:24.665 --> 00:13:26.665
I think 5 or 6.

131
00:13:26.667 --> 00:13:29.167
And AJ's dad lives here.

132
00:13:29.169 --> 00:13:31.069
Mohan.
Mum's older brother.


133
00:13:31.071 --> 00:13:32.937
<i>Is he the one who treated
your mum so badly?</i>


134
00:13:32.939 --> 00:13:35.273
Yeah. He's barely
said hello so far.


135
00:13:37.444 --> 00:13:39.944
I think dinner's ready.
I'll call you later.


136
00:13:39.946 --> 00:13:42.080
<i>I'm so glad to hear
your mum's doing better.</i>


137
00:13:42.082 --> 00:13:43.782
<i>Please send her my love.</i>

138
00:14:24.391 --> 00:14:26.057
It's a conch, you know?

139
00:14:26.059 --> 00:14:29.761
We blow it to ward off
evil spirits.


140
00:14:29.763 --> 00:14:33.164
Why your mother
doesn't do puja?


141
00:14:33.166 --> 00:14:36.034
She doesn't really keep up
with those traditions.


142
00:14:37.137 --> 00:14:39.370
So when she's better,

143
00:14:39.372 --> 00:14:41.940
you think you will be exploring
Kolkata with her?


144
00:14:41.942 --> 00:14:46.044
I expect she'll want to
get back to London in a hurry.


145
00:14:48.982 --> 00:14:50.815
Depends if she's up to it.

146
00:14:50.817 --> 00:14:52.751
- This is delicious.
- Thank you.


147
00:14:52.753 --> 00:14:56.354
This is ilish macher bhapa.
Did you have it before?


148
00:14:56.356 --> 00:14:59.791
No. I don't think I've ever
seen it on a restaurant menu.


149
00:14:59.793 --> 00:15:01.359
We mostly cook it at home.

150
00:15:01.361 --> 00:15:02.861
I don't think Ronnie's mother

151
00:15:02.863 --> 00:15:04.896
will cook something
like this at home.


152
00:15:04.898 --> 00:15:06.898
Why are you so sure of that?

153
00:15:08.235 --> 00:15:10.301
'Cause you said
she isn't interested


154
00:15:10.303 --> 00:15:11.536
in Bengali traditions.

155
00:15:11.538 --> 00:15:14.105
Oh.

156
00:15:14.107 --> 00:15:16.107
Well, whose fault is that?

157
00:15:17.444 --> 00:15:19.144
Uncle Mohan?

158
00:15:22.783 --> 00:15:24.916
What do you mean?

159
00:15:24.918 --> 00:15:27.352
What do you think I mean?

160
00:15:27.354 --> 00:15:29.387
Making these digs
at my mother,


161
00:15:29.389 --> 00:15:32.190
like she should be sorry
for leaving India.


162
00:15:32.192 --> 00:15:35.326
She didn't abandon you.
You abandoned her.


163
00:15:35.328 --> 00:15:37.529
What are you talking about?

164
00:15:37.531 --> 00:15:39.798
Please excuse us.

165
00:15:39.800 --> 00:15:41.399
Come.

166
00:15:49.376 --> 00:15:51.309
My mum married for love

167
00:15:51.311 --> 00:15:55.280
and apparently the man she loved
was the wrong caste.


168
00:15:55.282 --> 00:15:58.850
So your dad here
cut her dead.


169
00:15:58.852 --> 00:16:00.919
Even when my father died,

170
00:16:00.921 --> 00:16:03.321
and my mum was left
pregnant and alone,


171
00:16:03.323 --> 00:16:06.457
your dad shut the door
in her face.


172
00:16:06.459 --> 00:16:09.294
That's why she ran
to London to have me.


173
00:16:18.338 --> 00:16:21.940
Ronnie, who told you that?

174
00:16:21.942 --> 00:16:24.843
My mum.
Who do you think?


175
00:16:31.218 --> 00:16:32.417
What's this?

176
00:16:34.187 --> 00:16:39.991
This was taken on
your parents' wedding day.


177
00:16:39.993 --> 00:16:42.093
That's my dad there.

178
00:16:44.397 --> 00:16:47.332
And this one is you...

179
00:16:47.334 --> 00:16:50.401
in your parents'
Kolkata house.


180
00:17:04.150 --> 00:17:06.451
- Did you tell him I'm sorry?
- Yeah.


181
00:17:06.453 --> 00:17:09.454
But this is what he's like
when he's upset.


182
00:17:09.456 --> 00:17:11.189
He shuts everyone out.

183
00:17:12.325 --> 00:17:15.093
Hey, Ronnie,

184
00:17:15.095 --> 00:17:16.628
you smoke ganja?

185
00:17:17.931 --> 00:17:18.930
I can't understand why my mum

186
00:17:18.932 --> 00:17:21.532
made up all these lies.

187
00:17:21.534 --> 00:17:24.002
Maybe she lost it
after my father died.


188
00:17:29.242 --> 00:17:30.541
Ronnie...

189
00:17:33.980 --> 00:17:37.081
Your dad was still alive
when your mum left India.


190
00:17:38.285 --> 00:17:39.350
What?

191
00:17:41.354 --> 00:17:45.123
My dad said he would come around
asking all the time


192
00:17:45.125 --> 00:17:46.991
if we had heard from her.

193
00:17:46.993 --> 00:17:48.993
But I was just a kid, man.
I don't remember much.


194
00:17:48.995 --> 00:17:56.067
Wait. You're saying that my mum
left my dad here?


195
00:17:56.069 --> 00:17:58.937
I think after about
four or five years,


196
00:17:58.939 --> 00:18:01.606
he just stopped looking.

197
00:18:03.476 --> 00:18:07.512
I guess if he died,
it would have been later.


198
00:18:10.583 --> 00:18:14.419
Meaning he might still
be alive?


199
00:18:16.256 --> 00:18:18.656
You need to talk
to your mum, man.


200
00:18:56.162 --> 00:18:59.263
Mum? Mum? Hey!

201
00:18:59.265 --> 00:19:01.299
It's me.

202
00:19:01.301 --> 00:19:03.468
I'm so glad you're okay.

203
00:19:04.771 --> 00:19:07.171
Where am I?

204
00:19:08.208 --> 00:19:09.574
You're in a hospital, Mum.

205
00:19:09.576 --> 00:19:12.610
But you're gonna be fine.

206
00:19:12.612 --> 00:19:14.212
You're in Kolkata.

207
00:19:20.120 --> 00:19:22.120
- Ronnie.
- Yeah?


208
00:19:22.122 --> 00:19:24.589
You need to go.

209
00:19:24.591 --> 00:19:27.158
We'll leave as soon as
you're better, Mum, okay?


210
00:19:27.160 --> 00:19:30.328
No. Go now.

211
00:19:30.330 --> 00:19:33.064
Why?

212
00:19:34.334 --> 00:19:36.067
She's coming.

213
00:19:36.069 --> 00:19:37.201
Who is?

214
00:19:39.539 --> 00:19:41.606
Ronnie?

215
00:19:41.608 --> 00:19:44.042
It's okay, Mum, it's okay.
It's just a power cut.


216
00:19:44.044 --> 00:19:45.810
No, Ronnie, you need to go!

217
00:19:45.812 --> 00:19:48.246
You need to leave India. Go!

218
00:19:48.248 --> 00:19:50.081
Mum, I'm not gonna leave
without you, okay?


219
00:19:50.083 --> 00:19:52.617
- Go! Go! Go!
- Mum, Mum, I'm--


220
00:19:52.619 --> 00:19:55.119
Excuse me, my mum's
having some kind of fit.


221
00:19:55.121 --> 00:19:56.421
Can you please
come and help?


222
00:19:56.423 --> 00:19:58.523
Excuse me, sir,
I'm busy now, please.


223
00:20:00.060 --> 00:20:02.260
Nurse, I'm sorry
to bother you,


224
00:20:02.262 --> 00:20:04.295
but my mum is having
some kind of fit.


225
00:20:04.297 --> 00:20:06.664
Excuse me,
that patient needs help.


226
00:20:06.666 --> 00:20:08.099
I'll come in a minute.

227
00:20:44.137 --> 00:20:46.604
Mum. Mum?

228
00:20:53.713 --> 00:20:55.480
Help me!

229
00:21:05.859 --> 00:21:08.426
One of the last things
my mother said


230
00:21:08.428 --> 00:21:10.428
was that "she was coming."

231
00:21:10.430 --> 00:21:14.632
And you think she meant
this woman in the purple sari?


232
00:21:14.634 --> 00:21:18.169
Well, she didn't kill
your mother.


233
00:21:18.171 --> 00:21:21.539
She couldn't have made it
to the ground level so fast.


234
00:21:21.541 --> 00:21:24.408
Probably she was some
beggar woman passing by.


235
00:21:24.410 --> 00:21:27.612
What about the symbol she drew
in my mother's blood?


236
00:21:27.614 --> 00:21:30.314
Who knows?

237
00:21:30.316 --> 00:21:32.250
Maybe she was just a crazy.

238
00:21:35.321 --> 00:21:38.923
You know, you can't really
push someone from here.


239
00:21:38.925 --> 00:21:41.592
You have to pick them up
and then throw them down.


240
00:21:50.503 --> 00:21:51.702
Thanks.

241
00:21:59.679 --> 00:22:02.313
Your mother was here because
she ran in front of a car.


242
00:22:06.819 --> 00:22:08.819
My mother would never
kill herself.


243
00:22:08.821 --> 00:22:11.689
I talk to her every day.
She never said anything.


244
00:22:11.691 --> 00:22:14.926
I'm afraid they often don't.

245
00:22:14.928 --> 00:22:16.427
I'm sorry.

246
00:25:02.962 --> 00:25:04.028
What's this?

247
00:25:05.832 --> 00:25:07.498
It'll protect you.

248
00:25:09.535 --> 00:25:10.601
From what?

249
00:25:10.603 --> 00:25:13.104
They say it takes 13 days

250
00:25:13.106 --> 00:25:15.406
for your mother's soul
to leave this place.


251
00:25:15.408 --> 00:25:16.774
And in that time,

252
00:25:16.776 --> 00:25:19.643
her soul is attracted
towards her loved ones.


253
00:25:27.120 --> 00:25:28.786
Who's that?

254
00:25:41.701 --> 00:25:46.103
Excuse me, did you know
my mother, Suleka?


255
00:25:47.840 --> 00:25:49.840
You are her son?

256
00:25:52.845 --> 00:25:54.812
I am very sorry.

