523
00:56:57.742 --> 00:56:58.974
All of your keys and wallets

524
00:56:58.976 --> 00:57:01.844
should be in the tray
in front of you.


525
00:57:13.891 --> 00:57:15.491
Are you okay, sir?

526
00:57:15.493 --> 00:57:19.561
Sorry, excuse me.

527
00:58:10.981 --> 00:58:13.649
Fuck.

528
00:58:31.001 --> 00:58:34.636
My passport was in my bag, too,
including my phone.


529
00:58:34.638 --> 00:58:37.072
Okay. Why don't you
come into our office,


530
00:58:37.074 --> 00:58:38.841
and we can take a description
of the man and then--


531
00:58:38.843 --> 00:58:41.543
But my flight's closing.

532
00:58:41.545 --> 00:58:43.946
You're not getting
onto that flight, sir.


533
00:58:46.851 --> 00:58:49.385
I'm sorry to ask you.

534
00:58:49.387 --> 00:58:51.387
My uncle doesn't want me
at the house.


535
00:58:51.389 --> 00:58:53.789
You wait there.
I'll be coming.


536
00:58:53.791 --> 00:58:55.691
<i>Thank you, Asha.</i>

537
00:58:55.693 --> 00:58:56.725
No problem.

538
00:59:58.823 --> 01:00:00.022
Oh.

539
01:00:02.026 --> 01:00:04.059
Your clothes are probably dry.
One second.


540
01:00:04.061 --> 01:00:06.228
What happened?

541
01:00:06.230 --> 01:00:08.630
You passed out.

542
01:00:08.632 --> 01:00:10.599
I'm afraid you got sick
on your clothes,


543
01:00:10.601 --> 01:00:13.635
so I rinsed them.

544
01:00:13.637 --> 01:00:14.937
Here.

545
01:00:17.675 --> 01:00:19.808
How are you feeling now?

546
01:00:21.145 --> 01:00:22.244
Better.

547
01:00:22.246 --> 01:00:24.980
Thank you.

548
01:00:24.982 --> 01:00:27.916
I'll let you get dressed.
Sorry.


549
01:00:29.587 --> 01:00:31.787
This little girl
sold me a bottle of water.


550
01:00:31.789 --> 01:00:33.989
It's like she had me
marked out.


551
01:00:33.991 --> 01:00:36.825
It's a hard country
for people like you.


552
01:00:36.827 --> 01:00:38.594
Anything can take you down.

553
01:00:38.596 --> 01:00:42.798
But a man stole my bag,
passport, everything.


554
01:00:42.800 --> 01:00:46.268
I was puking up,
and he was there waiting.


555
01:00:49.039 --> 01:00:51.073
I sound completely paranoid,
right?


556
01:00:51.075 --> 01:00:52.574
No.

557
01:00:54.111 --> 01:00:56.178
Not completely.

558
01:00:56.180 --> 01:00:59.681
Did you give Detective Banerji
the newsreels?


559
01:00:59.683 --> 01:01:02.251
I did.

560
01:01:02.253 --> 01:01:05.754
But he has a dozen
open murder cases.


561
01:01:05.756 --> 01:01:07.756
He's not about to take up a case
from 30 years ago.


562
01:01:07.758 --> 01:01:09.091
But if it's coming from you--

563
01:01:09.093 --> 01:01:11.293
Especially
if it's coming from me.


564
01:01:11.295 --> 01:01:16.198
Were you and Detective Banerji
ever in a relationship?


565
01:01:16.200 --> 01:01:18.600
I saw a photo.

566
01:01:18.602 --> 01:01:21.603
I'm afraid we still are.

567
01:01:21.605 --> 01:01:22.905
He's my father.

568
01:01:24.708 --> 01:01:27.576
I don't usually tell people.

569
01:01:27.578 --> 01:01:30.145
I was a screw-up
when he got me the job.


570
01:01:30.147 --> 01:01:31.813
And where is your mum?

571
01:01:33.183 --> 01:01:35.083
My mum's not alive.

572
01:01:39.790 --> 01:01:44.159
Ronnie, are you still
looking for answers?


573
01:01:44.161 --> 01:01:46.862
What do you mean?

574
01:01:46.864 --> 01:01:49.331
I found the original
police file.


575
01:01:51.201 --> 01:01:54.069
The police did have
a suspect back then.


576
01:01:54.071 --> 01:01:56.738
Arun Das.

577
01:02:01.812 --> 01:02:04.246
<i>Arun Das.</i>

578
01:02:04.248 --> 01:02:06.715
<i>Arun Das.</i>

579
01:02:08.285 --> 01:02:10.152
Ronnie, maybe
we should leave this.


580
01:02:10.154 --> 01:02:11.153
No.

581
01:02:13.724 --> 01:02:15.257
He was a priest?

582
01:02:15.259 --> 01:02:16.258
In training.

583
01:02:16.260 --> 01:02:17.893
After they shot him,

584
01:02:17.895 --> 01:02:20.862
Arun Das was never seen again.

585
01:02:22.967 --> 01:02:24.299
So...

586
01:02:26.670 --> 01:02:28.670
How old was he
when they shot him?


587
01:02:28.672 --> 01:02:33.809
He was, uh... 28 then.

588
01:02:33.811 --> 01:02:36.244
The worst thing
is that all the victims


589
01:02:36.246 --> 01:02:38.080
were people he should have
cared about.


590
01:02:38.082 --> 01:02:40.015
I don't understand.

591
01:02:40.017 --> 01:02:41.750
Like relatives, loved ones.

592
01:02:41.752 --> 01:02:45.787
The last victim who ended up
brain damaged was...


593
01:02:45.789 --> 01:02:47.289
Arun's mother.

594
01:02:49.193 --> 01:02:51.727
- Does it say where he lived?
- In one of the slums.


595
01:02:51.729 --> 01:02:54.930
- Which slum?
- Um...


596
01:02:54.932 --> 01:02:55.998
Khalside.

597
01:02:57.735 --> 01:02:59.968
The rumor is he used
to spend nights there


598
01:02:59.970 --> 01:03:03.639
with a medium called, um...

599
01:03:03.641 --> 01:03:05.173
Rakhee.

600
01:03:11.115 --> 01:03:13.248
This is where
your mum was knocked over?


601
01:03:18.989 --> 01:03:21.857
Why do you think
she came here?


602
01:03:21.859 --> 01:03:23.258
I don't know.

603
01:03:24.328 --> 01:03:26.361
But it has to do
with Rakhee.


604
01:03:34.772 --> 01:03:38.006
- You know where you're going?
- Yeah, it's this way.


605
01:03:44.014 --> 01:03:46.248
- She sold me the water.
- What?


606
01:03:46.250 --> 01:03:48.817
At the airport.

607
01:03:48.819 --> 01:03:50.085
Ronnie!

608
01:03:51.321 --> 01:03:52.821
Wait!

609
01:03:52.823 --> 01:03:53.889
Wait!

610
01:03:58.762 --> 01:03:59.828
Wait!

611
01:04:03.734 --> 01:04:04.800
Stop!

612
01:04:39.169 --> 01:04:40.168
Hello?

613
01:04:42.473 --> 01:04:43.805
Hello?

614
01:04:55.953 --> 01:04:58.386
Ah, Ronnie, what happened?

615
01:04:58.388 --> 01:05:00.756
Some... Someone...

616
01:05:06.296 --> 01:05:08.363
This is the place.

617
01:06:29.112 --> 01:06:31.546
She's saying your mother
came in with this knife.


618
01:06:31.548 --> 01:06:33.348
Who was my mother looking for?

619
01:06:39.423 --> 01:06:40.422
Rakhee.

620
01:06:57.608 --> 01:06:58.607
Nah.

621
01:07:24.434 --> 01:07:27.002
Where is Rakhee now?
Is she alive?


622
01:07:30.607 --> 01:07:33.541
<i>Arun Das.</i>

623
01:07:37.047 --> 01:07:39.681
<i>Arun Das.</i>

624
01:08:03.941 --> 01:08:07.409
This is where the cop said
he shot him. Bullet hole.


625
01:08:07.411 --> 01:08:09.110
Look.

626
01:08:10.380 --> 01:08:12.948
This really could be Arun Das.

627
01:08:13.951 --> 01:08:15.717
<i>Arun Das.</i>

628
01:08:17.120 --> 01:08:18.520
<i>Arun Das.</i>

629
01:08:18.522 --> 01:08:21.156
Hey.

630
01:09:43.140 --> 01:09:44.472
Hello?

631
01:09:48.145 --> 01:09:50.111
Ronnie.

632
01:09:50.113 --> 01:09:52.380
My father caught
the Elgin House killer.


633
01:09:52.382 --> 01:09:55.150
They're at the station.

634
01:10:03.160 --> 01:10:05.794
How did you know
this was there?


635
01:10:05.796 --> 01:10:08.296
I don't know.

636
01:10:08.298 --> 01:10:09.798
What does it say?

637
01:10:09.800 --> 01:10:13.435
"Send seven souls to hell
in seven nights


638
01:10:13.437 --> 01:10:15.203
in place of my soul,

639
01:10:15.205 --> 01:10:18.339
so I can return forever,
Rakshasa."


640
01:10:18.341 --> 01:10:20.542
A Rakshasa is a demon king.

641
01:10:20.544 --> 01:10:22.710
Yes. This demon.

642
01:10:22.712 --> 01:10:25.346
Kali Yuga's coming.

643
01:10:28.085 --> 01:10:32.253
My mother knew
all about this stuff.


644
01:10:32.255 --> 01:10:34.255
It took ahold of her.

645
01:10:34.257 --> 01:10:35.757
What does it mean?

646
01:10:35.759 --> 01:10:39.094
There's a prophecy in the Vedas.

647
01:10:41.565 --> 01:10:43.131
Kali Yuga.

648
01:10:43.132 --> 01:10:44.698
A time when demons
walk the Earth again.


649
01:10:44.701 --> 01:10:47.535
Families kill each other.

650
01:10:47.537 --> 01:10:49.704
Apocalypse.

651
01:10:49.706 --> 01:10:54.776
If that's the ritual,
he failed.


652
01:10:54.778 --> 01:10:57.545
Arun didn't kill seven.

653
01:10:57.547 --> 01:11:00.482
Twenty-eight years ago.

654
01:11:00.484 --> 01:11:02.584
So who's your father arrested?

655
01:11:06.256 --> 01:11:08.123
Please.

656
01:11:17.667 --> 01:11:20.401
Family of the dead girl.

657
01:11:20.403 --> 01:11:21.569
Come in.

658
01:11:29.880 --> 01:11:31.546
Sit down.

659
01:11:44.594 --> 01:11:47.395
But he's just a boy.

660
01:11:54.304 --> 01:11:55.870
You're not allowed in here!

661
01:11:57.440 --> 01:11:59.440
I signed him in.

662
01:12:00.677 --> 01:12:03.378
Did this kid
really kill my mother?


663
01:12:03.380 --> 01:12:04.879
No.

664
01:12:04.881 --> 01:12:07.682
He just killed the girl,
Shugan Nagush.


665
01:12:07.684 --> 01:12:09.684
He has an alibi
for your mother's death.


666
01:12:09.686 --> 01:12:11.452
It checks out.

667
01:12:11.454 --> 01:12:14.889
But he painted the same symbol
over the girl's bed.


668
01:12:16.560 --> 01:12:19.427
Even if he painted it,
it's irrelevant.


669
01:12:19.429 --> 01:12:21.696
He was in a study group
when your mother died.


670
01:12:21.698 --> 01:12:23.264
Twenty people saw him.

671
01:12:23.266 --> 01:12:24.365
Then who drew it?

672
01:12:27.771 --> 01:12:33.208
After your mother's death,
you ran down to her body, right?


673
01:12:33.210 --> 01:12:34.509
This is bullshit.

674
01:12:34.511 --> 01:12:36.544
Papa, please.

675
01:12:37.914 --> 01:12:39.914
You need to look at this file.

676
01:12:43.286 --> 01:12:46.955
There was a series of murders
just like this in 1987.


677
01:12:46.957 --> 01:12:49.624
The same symbol was used.

678
01:12:49.626 --> 01:12:53.661
You are investigating my case
with the suspect?


679
01:12:53.663 --> 01:12:56.631
Read this file.

680
01:12:56.633 --> 01:12:58.967
All of this is connected
to the present-day murders.


681
01:12:58.969 --> 01:13:01.736
Have you gone completely crazy?

682
01:13:01.738 --> 01:13:05.607
You need to listen to us
or five more people may die.


683
01:13:05.609 --> 01:13:06.808
Enough!

684
01:13:14.751 --> 01:13:18.786
Shugan Nagush's family
needs a car home.


685
01:13:18.788 --> 01:13:20.255
Go. Call for one.

686
01:13:41.411 --> 01:13:42.877
Your mother's valuables.

687
01:13:42.879 --> 01:13:45.880
You can collect the clothes
from the front desk.


688
01:13:50.687 --> 01:13:52.320
What does this mean?

689
01:13:52.322 --> 01:13:54.422
Aren't you investigating it
anymore?


690
01:13:54.424 --> 01:13:57.425
We recovered the CCTV footage
from the hospital.


691
01:13:57.427 --> 01:14:00.361
Nobody went in
or out of the ward.


692
01:14:02.399 --> 01:14:03.831
I wanna watch that footage.

693
01:14:12.942 --> 01:14:14.976
Listen.

694
01:14:14.978 --> 01:14:19.714
The only person who could have
killed your mother is you.


695
01:14:19.716 --> 01:14:23.318
Now, I don't think
I can prove that,


696
01:14:23.320 --> 01:14:26.688
but if you like,
I can give it a damn good try.


697
01:15:26.516 --> 01:15:29.617
Asha, it's me, Ronnie.
I need to talk to you.


698
01:15:29.619 --> 01:15:32.153
I need your help
with something.


699
01:15:32.155 --> 01:15:35.423
I wanna talk to the family
of the girl that was murdered.


700
01:15:37.127 --> 01:15:39.594
The case has been closed,
Ronnie.


701
01:15:39.596 --> 01:15:41.396
He's not the real killer.

702
01:15:41.398 --> 01:15:42.897
My father suspended me
from duty.


703
01:15:42.899 --> 01:15:44.665
It's over.

704
01:15:44.667 --> 01:15:46.601
But that's not
what you believe, is it?


705
01:15:46.603 --> 01:15:49.537
I don't know
what I believe in anymore.


706
01:15:49.539 --> 01:15:51.672
That kid didn't do this.

707
01:15:51.674 --> 01:15:53.574
Your dad knows it.

708
01:15:53.576 --> 01:15:55.576
He just needed
to make an arrest.


709
01:15:55.578 --> 01:16:00.481
Why are you still doing this?
Maybe my father was right.


710
01:16:00.483 --> 01:16:02.483
You should just go back home
for your own good.


711
01:16:02.485 --> 01:16:03.518
I can't.

712
01:16:03.520 --> 01:16:05.853
If I just leave this,

713
01:16:05.855 --> 01:16:08.423
how do I know it won't
follow me back to England?


714
01:16:08.425 --> 01:16:12.593
The victims were all close
to the killer 28 years ago


715
01:16:12.595 --> 01:16:15.897
Maybe my Mum is somehow
connected to this girl's family?


716
01:16:25.108 --> 01:16:27.842
Write it down.
You have a pen?


717
01:16:27.844 --> 01:16:29.143
Yeah.

718
01:16:31.881 --> 01:16:33.548
It's Golback Road.

719
01:16:33.550 --> 01:16:36.083
45A Karun Apartments.

720
01:16:36.085 --> 01:16:38.219
The girl's father's name
is Roger Degosh.


721
01:16:39.789 --> 01:16:41.222
Roger?

722
01:16:41.224 --> 01:16:42.824
What is it?

723
01:17:24.968 --> 01:17:27.201
I'm very sorry to disturb you.

724
01:17:27.203 --> 01:17:29.704
May I talk to you
about your daughter Sekonia?


725
01:17:29.706 --> 01:17:32.840
Why? Who are you?

726
01:17:36.513 --> 01:17:38.880
My mother was killed.

727
01:17:38.882 --> 01:17:40.848
I think the same person
may be responsible.


728
01:17:44.721 --> 01:17:46.754
I'm sorry.

729
01:17:46.756 --> 01:17:48.623
Okay, come in.

730
01:17:48.625 --> 01:17:50.057
Hashminda!

731
01:17:50.059 --> 01:17:51.726
Come in 10 minutes.

732
01:18:03.239 --> 01:18:04.305
Come.

733
01:18:08.278 --> 01:18:11.646
Can I offer you
a cup of tea, uh...


734
01:18:11.648 --> 01:18:14.282
Mr. Degosh, may I show you
a picture of my mother?


735
01:18:38.308 --> 01:18:39.640
Ronnie?

736
01:18:46.182 --> 01:18:48.649
She told me you were dead.

737
01:19:16.079 --> 01:19:20.781
We keep on being told
that the power cuts will stop,


738
01:19:20.783 --> 01:19:24.919
but they really have been
getting worse.


739
01:19:27.757 --> 01:19:29.757
Why did Mum leave India?

740
01:19:35.231 --> 01:19:37.965
What did she tell you?

741
01:19:37.967 --> 01:19:41.969
The story I know now
is completely untrue.


742
01:19:41.971 --> 01:19:46.240
I didn't even know I was
born here until five days ago,


743
01:19:46.242 --> 01:19:48.843
when Uncle Mohan told me.

744
01:19:51.047 --> 01:19:53.948
What really happened?

745
01:19:53.950 --> 01:19:58.953
As soon as you were born,
you got very sick.


746
01:19:58.955 --> 01:20:02.356
The doctors were certain
that you wouldn't last the week.


747
01:20:02.358 --> 01:20:05.092
What was wrong with me?

748
01:20:05.094 --> 01:20:07.328
It was your heart.

749
01:20:07.330 --> 01:20:09.997
After four days,
the doctors told us


750
01:20:09.999 --> 01:20:14.802
that they were going to try
a last ditch operation,


751
01:20:14.804 --> 01:20:19.073
but... we must prepare
for the worst.


752
01:20:20.443 --> 01:20:22.977
But I got better.

753
01:20:22.979 --> 01:20:24.979
I survived.

754
01:20:24.981 --> 01:20:27.214
The scar on my chest
is from the operation.


755
01:20:36.426 --> 01:20:38.793
Your mother
used to go to séances.


756
01:20:38.795 --> 01:20:41.095
Did Mohan tell you that?

757
01:20:42.965 --> 01:20:46.233
Without telling me, she took you
from your hospital bed


758
01:20:46.235 --> 01:20:48.335
before they could operate.

759
01:20:48.337 --> 01:20:50.705
Where did she take me?

760
01:20:52.175 --> 01:20:57.144
I found her back at our flat
just before dawn,


761
01:20:57.146 --> 01:21:00.915
packing a suitcase,

762
01:21:00.917 --> 01:21:05.186
and you were lying
in a basket


763
01:21:05.188 --> 01:21:07.421
by her bed.

764
01:21:07.423 --> 01:21:12.426
You had a fresh scar
all the way down your chest.


765
01:21:12.428 --> 01:21:15.062
But you seemed...

766
01:21:15.064 --> 01:21:17.131
you seemed better.

767
01:21:17.133 --> 01:21:21.435
She took me to Rakhee,
didn't she?


768
01:21:28.177 --> 01:21:30.177
You know about her.

769
01:21:31.814 --> 01:21:34.982
Your mother told me
that Rakhee had cured you


770
01:21:34.984 --> 01:21:38.285
and that we had to leave India
right this moment.


771
01:21:38.287 --> 01:21:40.988
Go far away.

772
01:21:40.990 --> 01:21:42.890
I couldn't accept it.

773
01:21:42.892 --> 01:21:48.829
I told her I didn't believe
in witchcraft.


774
01:21:48.831 --> 01:21:50.931
I refused to leave.

775
01:21:50.933 --> 01:21:53.467
But when I woke up
the next morning,


776
01:21:53.469 --> 01:21:55.469
you were both gone.

777
01:21:57.540 --> 01:21:59.240
What did Rakhee do to me?

778
01:21:59.242 --> 01:22:01.208
I don't know.

779
01:22:01.210 --> 01:22:04.411
Tell me what my mum said.

780
01:22:07.784 --> 01:22:10.118
Tell me!

781
01:22:10.119 --> 01:22:12.453
All she said was that Rakhee
had brought you back to us


782
01:22:12.455 --> 01:22:14.221
from the other side.

783
01:22:43.820 --> 01:22:45.186
Hashminda?

784
01:22:56.933 --> 01:23:01.969
Arun's victims
were all close to him.


785
01:23:01.971 --> 01:23:05.306
This time they're all
close to me.


786
01:23:05.308 --> 01:23:08.275
My mum, my half-sister.

787
01:23:08.277 --> 01:23:11.378
AJ's kid had that dream
that he'd be killed.


788
01:23:14.217 --> 01:23:18.419
Seven souls in seven nights,
remember?


789
01:23:18.421 --> 01:23:21.021
That's what the scroll said.
It's gonna be okay.


790
01:23:21.023 --> 01:23:22.456
What?

791
01:23:22.458 --> 01:23:24.992
Your half-sister
was killed six days ago.


792
01:23:24.994 --> 01:23:27.428
This week ends in...

793
01:23:27.430 --> 01:23:29.530
four hours.

794
01:23:33.035 --> 01:23:34.034
Fuck.

795
01:23:35.972 --> 01:23:37.271
Ronnie.

796
01:23:39.575 --> 01:23:42.009
It's gonna be okay, okay?

797
01:23:43.980 --> 01:23:45.279
It's gonna be...

798
01:24:57.253 --> 01:24:59.219
Stop!

799
01:24:59.221 --> 01:25:00.321
Oh!

800
01:25:01.590 --> 01:25:04.558
What the fuck was that?

801
01:25:04.560 --> 01:25:05.960
I'm sorry.

802
01:25:07.129 --> 01:25:08.195
What happened?

803
01:25:08.197 --> 01:25:10.197
I don't know.

804
01:25:12.635 --> 01:25:16.270
<i>Ronnie...</i>

805
01:25:29.085 --> 01:25:32.619
Asha, it's me.

806
01:26:42.691 --> 01:26:44.091
Thank you.

807
01:27:31.107 --> 01:27:34.508
Excuse me, do you recognize
any of these buildings?


808
01:27:41.650 --> 01:27:44.585
I want you to find
this building.


809
01:27:44.587 --> 01:27:45.819
This one here.

810
01:28:09.812 --> 01:28:11.478
Please wait for me, okay?

811
01:28:11.480 --> 01:28:14.815
I will triple
what's on your meter, yeah?


812
01:30:29.852 --> 01:30:31.418
You killed them all.

813
01:30:33.989 --> 01:30:36.556
I don't speak Bengali.
I can only understand--


814
01:31:47.496 --> 01:31:49.496
Where did you hide it?

815
01:33:22.658 --> 01:33:24.791
What?

816
01:33:24.793 --> 01:33:26.593
What foreign girl?

817
01:33:39.942 --> 01:33:41.842
No.

818
01:33:41.844 --> 01:33:45.779
No! No!

819
01:33:51.753 --> 01:33:53.787
Oh, Jesus, you're here.

820
01:33:53.789 --> 01:33:55.622
AJ, it's me, Ronnie!

821
01:33:56.758 --> 01:33:58.592
Ronnie.

822
01:33:58.594 --> 01:33:59.893
Thank God, yeah.

823
01:33:59.895 --> 01:34:01.628
Where have you been?

824
01:34:01.630 --> 01:34:03.663
I got people looking for you
all over Kolkata.


825
01:34:03.665 --> 01:34:05.665
Come, come, come, come.

826
01:34:05.667 --> 01:34:07.167
I was really starting
to freak out


827
01:34:07.169 --> 01:34:09.236
when you didn't come home
before sundown.


828
01:34:09.238 --> 01:34:11.037
Hey, you want a drink
or what?


829
01:34:11.039 --> 01:34:13.540
- Where is she?
- Who?


830
01:34:13.542 --> 01:34:15.609
- Lena.
- Who's Lena?


831
01:34:15.611 --> 01:34:17.777
My girlfriend Lena from the UK.
She's here.


832
01:34:17.779 --> 01:34:20.580
No, man, there's no one here.

833
01:34:20.582 --> 01:34:22.616
Is she coming in tonight?

834
01:34:22.618 --> 01:34:25.652
No. Maybe.

835
01:34:27.289 --> 01:34:29.289
Let me get you a cup of tea.

836
01:34:29.291 --> 01:34:33.159
I just made some.
You look beat, bro.


837
01:34:33.161 --> 01:34:34.761
Sure.

838
01:34:39.635 --> 01:34:44.104
Give me Lena's flight details,
and I'll go get her myself.


839
01:34:44.106 --> 01:34:46.673
You remember how chaotic
the airport is.


840
01:34:58.053 --> 01:34:59.686
Lena!

841
01:35:02.324 --> 01:35:03.823
Lena.

842
01:35:05.694 --> 01:35:07.928
Ronnie?

843
01:35:07.930 --> 01:35:09.296
Thank God, man.

844
01:35:09.298 --> 01:35:12.299
Where have you been?

845
01:35:12.301 --> 01:35:13.633
What's the matter, bro?

846
01:35:22.978 --> 01:35:25.278
It's very easy to get lost
at the airport.


847
01:35:38.126 --> 01:35:40.060
What are you doing, man?

848
01:35:46.969 --> 01:35:48.735
- AJ, AJ...
- What?


849
01:35:50.172 --> 01:35:51.237
Where's Lena?

850
01:35:51.239 --> 01:35:53.640
AJ, AJ!

851
01:35:56.111 --> 01:35:58.244
Lena?

852
01:35:58.246 --> 01:36:00.046
Lena!

853
01:36:00.048 --> 01:36:02.315
Daddy's dead!

854
01:36:02.317 --> 01:36:04.084
He's lying in the kitchen!

855
01:36:04.086 --> 01:36:05.185
Lena!

856
01:36:05.187 --> 01:36:06.252
Is that a Bengali number?

857
01:36:06.254 --> 01:36:07.354
Yes, it's a three.

858
01:36:07.356 --> 01:36:09.222
- You're dreaming.
- Lena!


859
01:36:15.864 --> 01:36:16.963
Lena?

860
01:36:25.741 --> 01:36:28.041
Lena? Lena?

861
01:36:28.043 --> 01:36:30.276
Lena. Oh, my God.
Stay with me.


862
01:36:31.913 --> 01:36:34.648
Okay, Lena,
get your arm around me.


863
01:36:34.650 --> 01:36:38.685
You can do this. Come on.
One, two, three, go.


864
01:36:38.687 --> 01:36:40.887
Come on, stay with me.
Stay with me.


865
01:36:40.889 --> 01:36:43.056
Help! Help!
Please help me!


866
01:36:46.395 --> 01:36:48.194
Just hold onto my hand, okay?
Just hold onto my hand.


867
01:36:48.196 --> 01:36:49.329
Yeah, good.
You're doing great.


868
01:36:49.331 --> 01:36:51.164
Wait.

869
01:36:51.166 --> 01:36:52.799
What's he injecting into me?

870
01:36:52.801 --> 01:36:54.067
She is losing pressure.

871
01:36:54.069 --> 01:36:55.802
He's just doing his job, okay?

872
01:36:55.804 --> 01:36:57.070
You're gonna be fine, babe.

873
01:36:57.072 --> 01:36:59.239
I need to talk to you.

874
01:36:59.241 --> 01:37:02.042
Remember me...

875
01:37:02.044 --> 01:37:06.413
me talking to you in bed
after the gig?


876
01:37:06.415 --> 01:37:10.817
Yeah. You said that you
weren't sure about touring


877
01:37:10.819 --> 01:37:12.419
and that, um...

878
01:37:12.421 --> 01:37:14.454
and that you wanted us
to spend more time together.


879
01:37:14.456 --> 01:37:17.924
- Need to tell you something.
- What is it?


880
01:37:17.926 --> 01:37:20.026
I'm pregnant.

881
01:37:32.874 --> 01:37:34.841
Lena! Lena! Lena!

882
01:37:34.843 --> 01:37:36.409
Lena! Oh, my God.

883
01:37:39.047 --> 01:37:41.214
No, no, no, no, no.

884
01:38:00.802 --> 01:38:03.903
No. No!

885
01:38:04.906 --> 01:38:05.939
No!

886
01:38:34.936 --> 01:38:36.402
<i>Kali Yuga's coming.</i>

887
01:38:36.404 --> 01:38:40.340
<i>A time when demons
walk the Earth again.</i>


888
01:38:40.342 --> 01:38:42.509
<i>Families kill each other.</i>

889
01:38:42.511 --> 01:38:44.477
<i>Apocalypse.</i>

890
01:38:56.091 --> 01:38:57.257
No.

891
01:38:59.361 --> 01:39:01.361
I'm not gonna let you win.

892
01:40:56.011 --> 01:40:58.144
No! No!

893
01:40:58.146 --> 01:40:59.345
No! Stop it!

894
01:40:59.347 --> 01:41:00.546
No, please!